<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h1>Data submission form</h1>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p><strong>Important information before you submit:</strong></p>

                    <p>If you have any special requests (e.g. access to reviewers only, or I need this request to be processed urgently) please
                        indicate this in the 'Additional information' field at the bottom of the form.</p>

                    <p>If you have any problems filling in the form, or if you would like to give us any feedback on the form,
                        please <a href="mailto:info@data.xxxxxxx.ac.uk">contact us</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <form id="data_form" class="form-horizontal" data-parsley-validate>

            <h2>Background</h2>

            <div class="form-group">
                <div class="col-md-7">
                    <strong>Was the data you intend to submit created in a project funded by an external entity or in collaboration with an external entity? *</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-2">
                    <input type="radio" name="external_funding" id="external_funding_yes" value="true"
                           data-parsley-required="true"
                           data-read="true" data-read-type="single">
                    <label for="external_funding_yes" class="control-label" style="text-align:left; margin-right: 10px">
                        Yes
                    </label>
                    <br>
                    <input type="radio" name="external_funding" id="external_funding_no" value="false"
                           data-parsley-required="true"
                           data-read="true" data-read-type="single">
                    <label for="external_funding_no" class="control-label" style="text-align:left;">
                        No
                    </label>
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="form-group">
                <div class="col-md-7">
                    <strong>Do your data contain any personal/sensitive, commercially-sensitive or other forms of confidential/restricted information? *</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-2">
                    <input type="radio" name="confidential_information" id="confidential_information_yes" value="true"
                           data-parsley-required="true"
                           data-read="true" data-read-type="single">
                    <label for="confidential_information_yes" class="control-label" style="text-align:left; margin-right: 10px">
                        Yes
                    </label>
                    <br>
                    <input type="radio" name="confidential_information" id="confidential_information_no" value="false"
                           data-parsley-required="true"
                           data-read="true" data-read-type="single">
                    <label for="confidential_information_no" class="control-label" style="text-align:left;">
                        No
                    </label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
                    <p><strong>Information about personal/sensitive information</strong> For information about personal/sensitive information have a look <a href="http://www.data.xxxxxxx.ac.uk/sensitive-data">here</a>.
                        If you have any doubts about this question, please consult <a href="http://www.xxxxxx.ac.uk/research-ethics">the University Ethics pages</a> or e-mail
                        <a href="mailto:info@admin.xxxxxxx.ac.uk">the Universityâ€™s Research Governance and Integrity Officer</a>.</p>

                    <p><strong>Information about other forms of confidential/restricted information</strong> Examples of other forms of
                        confidential/restricted information might include cases where there were confidentiality/publication
                        restrictions in sponsorship agreements or in collaborations agreements, or for example research data
                        which is subject to UK export control law.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="confidential_information_optional" style="display:none">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="accessrights" class="control-label col-md-4" style="text-align: left;">
                        Please explain the nature of confidential/restricted information in your data:*
                    </label>
                    <div class="col-md-7">
                        <textarea class="form-control" name="accessrights" id="accessrights" style="min-height:200px;"
                                  data-parsley-validate-if-empty="true" data-parsley-required-if-checked="#confidential_information_yes" data-parsley-required-if-checked-message="This value is required"
                                  data-read="true" data-read-type="single" data-read-if-checked="#confidential_information_yes"></textarea>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2>Rights</h2>

            <div class="form-group">
                <div class="col-md-7">
                    <label for="confirm_sharing_rights" class="control-label" style="text-align:left">
                        I confirm that I have the rights to share these data via the University Research Repository. *
                    </label>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-2">
                    <input type="checkbox" name="confirm_sharing_rights" id="confirm_sharing_rights" value="true" style="margin-top: 12px"
                           data-parsley-required="true" data-parsley-required-message="You must confirm"
                           data-read="true" data-read-type="single">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
                    <p>Please confirm that to the best of your knowledge you have obtained permissions for sharing of these data
                        from any third parties who might hold rights over these data and that you have the rights to share
                        these data via the University Research Repository.</p>

                    <p><strong>Unsure whether to tick or not?</strong></p>

                    <p>If you have any doubts about this statement, please consult (in the given order):</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>the Principal Investigator responsible for this study (if you are not the Principal Investigator)</li>
                        <li>your Departmental Administrator (or equivalent)</li>
                        <li>the appropriate Contracts Manager at the Research Operations Office.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

